This Grand China at W. Ann Road is now under new management and it was pretty good the last 2 times I have been there; within 2 weeks.
They have also renamed it to Great China and lowered the prices on their lunch specials.
I think my Kung Pao Chicken, rice, eggroll and hot-n-sour soup was $5.45   The food was good, service much better and it is very clean inside.
This is a big improvement from half a year ago when the prior owners had started to let the place really go down hill.
I am glad the new owners have come in and turned the place around because I was craving a good place to get my Chinese out on the NW side of town.

